$git --version
------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** This is not a git command. touch is used to create files in directory
$ touch index.html 
------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** This will initialize current directory as Local Repository
$ git init
------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** Add your name and Email address to git
$ git config --global user.name 'Bahram Behzadi'
$ git config --global user.email 'behzadi-fard@gmx.de'
------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** Add file(s) to Stage area
$ git add index.html
$ git add *.html  -> will add all files with .html extenstion to the stage area
$ git add .       -> will add all files to stage area
------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** Remove file from Stage area
$ git rm --cached index.html
------------------------------------------------------------------------

*** Commit
$ git commit -m 'comment comes here'
------------------------------------------------------------------------



*** Branches
$ git branch desk
$ git checkout desk

-----> How branches work:

1- make new branch
2- make your changes
3- add all changes to stage area
4- commit all
5- now, if you switch back to master branch you will see no changes. 
6- merge new edited branch while you are in master

------------------------------------------------------------------------




*** Define remote Repository to git
1- make an account in github
2- $ git remote add origin https://github.com/behzadifard/behzadifard.github.io 
3- $ git push -u origin master
------------------------------------------------------------------------





*** Clone 
$ git clone address....
------------------------------------------------------------------------



*** Pull -> if someone makes changes on master branch you can uptodate your branch
$ git pull
------------------------------------------------------------------------